  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Pat the <strong>pork belly</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Score the <strong>fatty side</strong> of the <strong>pork belly</strong> in a criss-cross pattern by drawing a sharp knife through the skin, deep enough to reach the meat below</p><p>Season with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and rub it deep into the criss-cross pattern</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679409160838-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679409160838-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679409160838-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679409160838-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679409160838-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a very high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>pork belly</strong>, fat side down and cook for 4 min or until golden and crispy, then flip and cook for 2 min on the other side</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>pork</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray, reserving the pan</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 35 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679409168157-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679409168157-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679409168157-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679409168157-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679409168157-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pork belly is cooking, top, tail, peel and slice the <strong>carrots</strong> finely on the diagonal</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679409173591-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679409173591-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679409173591-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679409173591-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679409173591-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>cornflour</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>in a small bowl with the <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tamari honey sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679409179094-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679409179094-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679409179094-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679409179094-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679409179094-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679409632672-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679409632672-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679409632672-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679409632672-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679409632672-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>carrot slices</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the<strong> sliced garlic </strong>and <strong>spinach </strong>and cook, covered, for a further 4-5 min or until the spinach is wilted</p><p>Once the spinach is wilted, drizzle over the <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> – this is your <strong>sesame garlic veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679409197399-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
